      <section id="id3566974">
        <title>[LO 4.1.2] </title>
        <para id="id8290670">Your idea might be brilliant and smart, but you will need a business plan if you want to get it going. A business plan is like a road map - it shows you where you are going and keeps you on track.</para>
        <para id="id3759004">Using your best <emphasis effect="bold">idea</emphasis>, consider the following <emphasis effect="bold">FOUR</emphasis> business basics:</para>
        <para id="id3759609"><emphasis effect="bold">What</emphasis> do I intend doing?</para>
        <para id="id1171529115075"><emphasis effect="bold">How</emphasis> do I intend doing it?</para>
        <para id="id4357684"><emphasis effect="bold">When</emphasis> do I intend doing it?</para>
        <para id="id2222985"><emphasis effect="bold">Why</emphasis> do I think this will succeed?</para>
        <para id="id2575150">Imagine you are planning to start the <emphasis effect="italics">Afribike</emphasis> venture. Draw up a simple business plan by filling in the answers in the table below. </para>
        <table id="id7671776" summary="">
          <tgroup cols="1">
            <colspec colnum="1" colname="c1"/>
            <tbody>
              <row>
                <entry>AFRIBIKE</entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>
                  <list id="id1171522219190" list-type="enumerated" number-style="arabic">
                    <item>What are we going to do?</item>
                  </list>
                </entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>2. How/where are we going to get bicycles to sell? </entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>3. When are we going to sell these bicycles? </entry>
              </row>
              <row>
                <entry>4. Why is our scheme sure to succeed?</entry>
              </row>
            </tbody>
          </tgroup>
        </table>
